{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\nPlan-review findings can tell a client to comply with rebar-internal identifiers such as \"ADR 0043.\" Those ADRs live in the rebar source repository, are not part of a client project's architecture record, and are not meaningful or necessarily accessible to the plan author. The defect is currently grounded in bundled reviewer instructions including src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_E2.md, plan_review_E6.md, plan_review_F1.md, plan_review_T13.md, plan_review_T14.md, and plan_review_hedge.md, plus deterministic operator-attested coaching in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_operator_attested.py and src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Initialize or open a client repository that uses rebar but does not contain rebar's docs/adr files.\n2. Create a work ticket whose acceptance criteria require ticket-recorded operational evidence without the [operator-attested] tag.\n3. Run rebar review-plan for that ticket with the bundled plan-review criteria.\n4. Observe a finding or suggested fix that justifies the required tag by citing \"ADR 0043\" or \"ADR-0043.\"\n\n## Expected Behavior\nThe finding explains the applicable rule in self-contained language: operational evidence recorded on the ticket requires the exact [operator-attested] tag and concrete specifics. It does not require the client to know or locate a rebar-internal ADR.\n\n## Actual Behavior\nReviewer prompt text and deterministic coaching can emit rebar-internal ADR identifiers in client-facing findings, impacts, suggested fixes, remediation, or coaching.\n\n## Approach\nReplace rebar-internal ADR citations in reviewer-facing prompt instructions and deterministic finding/coaching templates with self-contained plain-language rules. Preserve the underlying behavior, such as requiring the exact [operator-attested] tag and concrete ticket evidence, but explain it without assuming knowledge of rebar's design history.\n\nAdd a portability regression that runs plan review against a fixture client repository with no rebar docs/adr tree and asserts that reviewer-authored finding, impact, suggested-fix, remediation, and coaching text contains no rebar-internal ADR identifier. Add a source-level contract test covering bundled plan-review prompt text and deterministic user-facing message templates so future internal provenance references cannot leak into client output. Internal Python comments, rebar's own ADR documents, and client-authored/cited ADRs that exist in the target repository remain allowed.\n\nRejected: shipping or linking rebar's ADR corpus to every client. That would expose implementation history instead of making findings self-contained and would still couple client guidance to rebar internals.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_E2.md\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_E6.md\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_F1.md\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T13.md\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T14.md\n- src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_hedge.md\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_operator_attested.py\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py\n- tests/unit/test_plan_review_portability.py\n\n## Testing\n- Deterministic path: an untagged operational-evidence AC still produces actionable coaching, but no rebar ADR identifier.\n- LLM prompt path: the fixture client has no rebar ADR files; generated finding fields state the applicable rule in plain language.\n- Source contract: bundled plan-review prompt bodies and deterministic client-facing templates reject rebar-internal ADR tokens while permitting internal code comments and an ADR citation grounded in a client fixture.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An operator-attested plan-review fixture produces the same criterion decision before and after the wording change; verified by pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_portability.py.\n- [ ] Reviewer-authored finding, impact, suggested_fix, remediation, and coaching fields for a client fixture with no rebar ADR files contain no rebar-internal ADR identifier; verified by pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_portability.py.\n- [ ] Bundled plan-review prompt bodies and deterministic user-facing message templates contain no rebar-internal ADR citation; verified by pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_portability.py.\n- [ ] A client-authored ADR citation backed by a file in the target repository remains eligible as grounded evidence; verified by pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_portability.py.\n- [ ] Internal implementation comments and docs/adr files remain outside the portability restriction; verified by the source-contract test's explicit scan scope.\n- [ ] The default non-integration suite exits zero; verified by pytest -m \"not integration and not external\" -q."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784507557575297001,"uuid":"4ad1867b-e6f3-42e7-b39f-a9c6fb20605b"}